<section xml:id="section-introduction-to-metric-geometry" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>
    Introduction to Metric Geometry
  </title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      To begin, we introduce a generalization of our usual notion of distance which is called a <term> metric </term>. The properties of physical distance make it an extremely useful tool for formalizing the analytical notions mentioned above.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <xi:include href="./subsection-introduction-to-metrics.ptx"/>

  <xi:include href="./subsection-constructing-new-metrics.ptx"/>

  <xi:include href="./subsection-normed-vector-spaces.ptx"/>

  <conclusion>
    <p>
      In the next section, we introduce one of the most important ideas in the field of analysis: that of convergence to a limit.
    </p>
  </conclusion>

  <xi:include href="./exercises/exercises-introduction-to-metric-geometry.ptx"/>

